04/05/2011
WASHINGTON, United States -- The US welcome Croatia's progress in the EU integration process, Croatian President Ivo Josipovic said on Tuesday (May 3rd), after talks at the White House with Vice-President Joe Biden. Josipovic added that the main topics were bilateral relations, co-operation within NATO and fighting terrorism. He also met with Secretary of State Hillary Clinton, who voiced support for the country's EU bid. (HRT, Hina, Nova TV - 02/05/11)
